min:
"The Heights" is a diverse neighborhood in Jersey City. Local grocery, limited restaurant/deli and liquor stores are within a 5-20 minute walk. There are also two urban parks, Pershing Field and Gordon Park, that are a quick walk from the house. Pershing field has playground equipment, tennis courts and other amenities.

Please note "the Heights" is not in the downtown area of Jersey City that borders the Hudson River. The Heights is primarily residential, rather than a commercial neighborhood. You can reach Jersey City's waterfront via 2 subway stops, Grove Street or Exchange Place or take a taxi there.

If you want local 'action' in the evening, this is probably not the right property for you. If you want a large number of trendy restaurants, bars, high end shops within a 5 minute walk, this is probably not the right property for you.

Our listing is in a residential, quiet neighborhood.

Hello, and welcome to our home. My husband and I would be so happy to host you in our newly constructed Jersey City condo. We both share a huge passion for travel, and we have been blessed to live and visit many places all over the world. Chris and I decided to root ourselves in the city that has so much to offer which is Jersey City. While settling here, we decided to give our fellow travel lovers a place that feels like home. With southern hospitality in our roots, we have a deep love for hosting, and we look forward to extending that love and warmth to our new friends.
Our modern, sun-drenched condo offers a tranquil vibe, which is perfect to come home to after a long day of exploring the city. This location is perfect for families who want to visit Jersey City  or New York area. The location is prime for any sports enthusiasts as we are a quick fifteen-minute drive to MetLife stadium‚Äîhome of the New York Giants and New York Jets.
